"Abstract The media circus turned on itself earlier this year following Naomi Campbell’s victory in Naomi Campbell v Mirror Group Newspapers [2002] EWHC (QB) which saw Piers Morgan in the dock defending his rights to publish. Defeated and forced to pay her compensation, the newspaper announced that it would consider an appeal. The outcome of this is awaited. In the meantime, IT and e-commerce lawyers Nigel Wildish and Marcus Turle of City law firm Field Fisher Waterhouse discuss the story so far…"
